<article data-view="I4" contenteditable="true" tabindex="1"><h1>Signals</h1><div>A <span style="font-style: italic;">signal </span>signifies a communication within the framework.&nbsp; There are different types of signals that identifies the communication method "channel" that the signal propagation is traversing. For example:</div><div><ul><li>Apply:</li><li>Call:</li><li>Message:</li><li>Event:</li><li>Broadcast:&nbsp;</li></ul></div><div><br></div><div>The signal data is carried through a <span style="font-style: italic;">message.&nbsp; </span>A message can be a string identifying the signal's <span style="font-style: italic;">topic </span>or any mutable object with a <span style="font-weight: bold;">topic </span>property.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>An <span style="font-style: italic;">Owner </span>is a receiver that receives messages and propagates them within its ownership scope.&nbsp; Owners have a signal object whose methods perform the propagation.&nbsp; For example:<br></div><div><ul><li><span style="text-decoration-line: underline;">owner.signal.Message</span></li></ul><span style="font-family: sans-serif;"><div><span style="font-family: sans-serif;"><br></span></div>is the method to propagate a Message signal.&nbsp; When a message is propagated, it is assigned a Symbol.Signal property identifying the signal/propagation.</span><br></div><div><span style="font-family: sans-serif;"><br></span></div><div><div>As signals propagate, the message is sent to&nbsp;<span style="font-style: italic;">receiver&nbsp;</span>nodes within the channel graph.&nbsp; A receiver is any&nbsp;object with a&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: bold;">receive</span>(message)<span style="font-weight: bold;">&nbsp;</span>method.&nbsp; The receiver determines whether it will interact with the message through the topic and other state within a message object.</div><div><br></div><div>A control is a receiver that delegates some or all signal processing to its <span style="font-weight: bold;">controller.process</span> method.</div></div></article>